main event: Object observed at 7:30 hrs 4 July 1963 at an estimated distance of 1,500-2,000 yards. It was stationary and emitting a light at 041310Z bearing 185 deg 9t deg altitude.
interesting points: The object was observed for 12 minutes.
The object was stationary and emitting a light.
The report indicates the object was 'bringing itself to a horizontal position as it approached the witness'.
The case is evaluated as a 'PHOTO SIGHTING' even though no photographs were taken.
The report also mentions a 'SIGHTING POSITIVELY INST 3520.3'.
